# Smart Menu — Project Rules for Cascade

## Identity
SaaS restaurant management platform. Multi-tenant (one User → many Restaurants).
Deployed on Heroku. PostgreSQL + Redis + Memcached.

## Tech Stack
- Ruby 3.3.10, Rails 7.2.2, PostgreSQL 14+
- Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus), importmap-rails + esbuild, SCSS (cssbundling-rails)
- Devise + OmniAuth (Google/Apple/Spotify), Pundit authorization, Flipper feature flags
- Sidekiq 7 (Redis), ActionCable (Redis), Memcached (Dalli/IdentityCache)
- Payments: Stripe 13.x + Square REST v2 (dual-provider)
- AI: OpenAI (GPT-4o, DALL-E), Google Cloud Vision (OCR), DeepL (translation)
- File uploads: Shrine + Active Storage, AWS S3
- Monitoring: Sentry 5.12

## CRITICAL Naming Conventions (non-standard — do NOT guess standard Rails names)
- `Ordr` not Order — model, table `ordrs`, controller `OrdrsController`
- `Ordritem` not OrderItem — model, table `ordritems`, controller `OrdritemsController`
- `Ordritemnote` — table `ordritemnotes`
- `Ordrparticipant` — table `ordrparticipants`
- `Ordraction` — table `ordractions`
- `Menusection` not MenuSection — model, table `menusections`
- `Menuitem` not MenuItem — model, table `menuitems`
- `Menuparticipant` — table `menuparticipants`
- `Tablesetting` not Table — model, table `tablesettings`
- `Allergyn` not Allergen — model, table `allergyns`
- Price field on ordritem: `ordritemprice` (not `price` or `unit_price`)
- Status fields use integer enums (e.g., `opened: 0, ordered: 20, paid: 35`)

